</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Plank Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Assume a prone position on a suitable mat or padded area. You can also use the ground.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your elbows and the balls of your feet should be in contact with the ground. There should be a straight line from your head to your heels. Your head should be facing the ground.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Engage your core. Hold the position for the stated sets and time.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid letting your hips sag or come up throughout. Keep your core engaged to maintain the straight position.</li>



<li>Focus on a point on the floor directly in front of you. Avoid letting your head tuck or extend excessively to limit potential neck strain.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



