<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Best 30-Minute Calisthenics Workout Routine</h2>



<p>To help you out, weâ€™ve chosen five exercises from above and programmed them into a 30-minute calisthenics routine. This routine is designed to improve your cardiovascular fitness and general conditioning.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Aim to perform this routine 3â€“4 times a week with three rest days in between. This can be evenly divided over a two-week period.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The mix of high-intensity dynamic exercises requires <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38689583/#:~:text=Systemic%20resistance%20training%20aims%20to,recovery%20may%20temporarily%20impair%20performance." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">adequate rest and recovery</a> even though youâ€™re using body weight. A weighted vest can be used to increase the exercise intensity where needed.</p>



<p>An example routine could look like this:</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Monday â€” </strong>30-Minute Calisthenics Workout.</li>



<li><strong>Tuesday â€” </strong>Rest Day.</li>



<li><strong>Wednesday â€” </strong>30-Minute Calisthenics Workout.</li>



<li><strong>Thursday â€” </strong>Rest Day.</li>



<li><strong>Friday â€” </strong>30-Minute Calisthenics Workout.</li>



<li><strong>Saturday â€” </strong>Rest Day,</li>



<li><strong>Sunday â€” </strong>30-Minute Calisthenics Workout.</li>
</ul>



<p>In the second week, Monday would be the rest day with Tuesday being the first working day. This provides <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6303131/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">sufficient training volume</a> while allowing for <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6719818/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">enough rest and recovery</a>.</p>



