<h2 class="wp-block-heading faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1623393125914"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Is 30 minutes of calisthenics enough?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Performing a 30-minute calisthenics routine is enough time when the main training principles are correctly applied. Ensure sufficient training volume and increase the intensity with weighted movements.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733224858393"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How many calories do 30 minutes of calisthenics burn?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">The exact amount depends on your weight, volume performed, and intensity used. However, expect to burn 200 calories on average for a 30-minute calisthenics session.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733224858989"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Is it OK to do calisthenics 5 days a week?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Calisthenics can be performed five days a week if needed. However, depending on the training volume and intensity, this may lead to less recovery time. Split the exercises into five-minute periods throughout the day to reduce possible fatigue.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733224860008"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Is calisthenics better than the gym?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Calisthenics training is not better or worse than the gym. Itâ€™s an alternative training method that offers several unique benefits. These include better function, less equipment, and lower or no cost.</p> </div> </div>
